---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import SiteHeader from "../components/SiteHeader.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import Prose from "../components/Prose.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy · Breaks"
  description="Breaks collects nothing. No analytics, no telemetry, no network. Everything stays on your Mac."
  canonicalPath="/privacy"
>
  <SiteHeader />
  <main>
    <Prose
      eyebrow="Privacy"
      title="We collect nothing."
      updated="28 April 2026"
    >
      <p>
        Breaks runs entirely on your Mac. The app does not send anything to us, to
        any third party, or anywhere else. There is no account, no sign-in, no
        email gate. Nothing about how you use Breaks leaves your machine.
      </p>

      <h2>What stays on your device</h2>
      <p>
        Breaks stores its settings and history in macOS <code>UserDefaults</code>
        under the bundle identifier <code>com.gjinprelvukaj.Breaks</code>. That
        includes your timer durations, focus journal entries, streak history,
        sounds, hotkeys, break suggestions, optional calendar export settings,
        and similar preferences. None of it is transmitted.
      </p>
      <p>
        Notifications, when enabled, are delivered locally by macOS. Breaks does
        not generate push notifications from a server.
      </p>
      <p>
        Calendar export, when enabled, writes completed focus sessions to the
        calendar you choose through Apple's local EventKit APIs. Breaks does not
        upload those events or read them for analytics.
      </p>

      <h2>What we don't collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>No analytics, no metrics, no telemetry.</li>
        <li>No crash reports sent to us.</li>
        <li>No advertising identifiers, ever.</li>
        <li>No location, contacts, photos, or files.</li>
        <li>No calendar access unless you turn on Calendar export.</li>
        <li>No accounts, emails, names, or device identifiers.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>This website</h2>
      <p>
        The site you're reading is hosted on GitHub Pages and serves static HTML,
        CSS, and a couple of fonts. It uses no cookies, no analytics, and no
        third-party trackers. GitHub may keep standard server-side request logs
        for the hosting itself; those logs are governed by
        <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" rel="noopener" target="_blank">GitHub's own privacy statement</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>App downloads</h2>
      <p>
        When you download a release, GitHub serves the file. GitHub may log that
        download server-side. Once the app is on your Mac, there's no further
        contact between Breaks and us.
      </p>

      <h2>Your data, your control</h2>
      <p>
        To wipe everything Breaks knows about you, run this in Terminal:
      </p>
      <p><code>defaults delete com.gjinprelvukaj.Breaks</code></p>
      <p>
        That clears all preferences and journal data. Uninstall by dragging
        Breaks.app out of <code>/Applications</code>.
      </p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        Breaks is intended for general audiences. Because we collect nothing, no
        information about anyone, including children, is gathered.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        If this policy changes, the updated date at the top of this page will
        change too. Substantive changes will be noted in the project changelog
        on GitHub.
      </p>

      <h2>Questions</h2>
      <p>
        Open an issue on
        <a href="https://github.com/GjinPrelvukaj/Breaks/issues" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
        and we'll respond there.
      </p>
    </Prose>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
